1
00:01:29,600 --> 00:01:33,070
[Cage of Shadows]

2
00:01:33,780 --> 00:01:36,259
[Episode 8]

3
00:01:36,800 --> 00:01:38,120
Golden Cave Guessing Game.

4
00:01:38,120 --> 00:01:38,960
Round one.

5
00:01:41,240 --> 00:01:41,920
Begin.

6
00:01:46,200 --> 00:01:47,729
Golden Cave Guessing Game.

7
00:01:47,870 --> 00:01:49,190
What exactly is it?

8
00:02:05,760 --> 00:02:06,560
Can she really

9
00:02:06,560 --> 00:02:08,360
tell the dice by sound?

10
00:02:19,079 --> 00:02:20,120
Please, God,

11
00:02:20,120 --> 00:02:22,000
watch over me.

12
00:02:22,020 --> 00:02:23,720
Buddha, Bodhisattva Guanyin,

13
00:02:23,720 --> 00:02:24,570
I beg you.

14
00:02:24,590 --> 00:02:26,520
No more touching once it's shaken.

15
00:02:40,079 --> 00:02:40,880
Open it.

16
00:03:04,400 --> 00:03:05,880
I survived.

17
00:03:05,880 --> 00:03:07,360
I survived!

18
00:03:06,710 --> 00:03:09,240
[Token]

19
00:03:12,720 --> 00:03:14,140
I survived.

20
00:03:15,720 --> 00:03:17,720
What good are last-minute prayers?

21
00:03:17,840 --> 00:03:19,170
When your luck is bad,

22
00:03:19,280 --> 00:03:20,880
even the gods can't save you.

23
00:03:21,590 --> 00:03:22,579
I'm doomed.

24
00:03:23,440 --> 00:03:25,000
You must have made a mistake.

25
00:03:25,000 --> 00:03:25,840
Let go of me!

26
00:03:25,840 --> 00:03:26,820
Let me go!

27
00:03:26,850 --> 00:03:27,730
Let me go!

28
00:03:27,840 --> 00:03:29,980
Let go! Let go of me!

29
00:03:36,079 --> 00:03:37,000
Stay away.

30
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:38,400
Don't come any closer.

31
00:03:38,420 --> 00:03:39,420
Stay back,

32
00:03:39,450 --> 00:03:40,810
or I won't go easy on you!

33
00:03:40,920 --> 00:03:41,780
Stay back!

34
00:03:41,870 --> 00:03:42,750
Let me go!

35
00:03:44,240 --> 00:03:45,320
You've made a mistake.

36
00:03:45,320 --> 00:03:47,200
Did you grab the wrong person?

37
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:49,120
Let me go!

38
00:03:49,480 --> 00:03:50,520
Dao.

39
00:03:53,740 --> 00:03:54,960
Don't be afraid.

40
00:03:55,040 --> 00:03:56,400
I clearly won.

41
00:03:56,400 --> 00:03:58,040
Why are you killing me?

42
00:03:58,060 --> 00:03:59,450
Because you're stupid.

43
00:03:59,480 --> 00:04:01,280
You're not following the rules.

44
00:04:01,280 --> 00:04:03,280
My roll was clearly higher.

45
00:04:03,390 --> 00:04:05,560
Are you sure you understand the rules?

46
00:04:05,880 --> 00:04:07,650
Please, don't kill me.

47
00:04:07,680 --> 00:04:10,580
I can stay here
and serve you like a slave.

48
00:04:10,910 --> 00:04:11,760
Me too.

49
00:04:11,760 --> 00:04:12,400
Me too.

50
00:04:12,400 --> 00:04:13,710
Please don't kill me.

51
00:04:13,740 --> 00:04:15,540
Then as you wish.

52
00:04:17,870 --> 00:04:20,470
Send them to the underworld
to serve as slaves.

53
00:04:20,760 --> 00:04:21,630
No!

54
00:04:21,660 --> 00:04:22,780
Don't kill me!

55
00:04:22,800 --> 00:04:23,800
No!

56
00:04:24,010 --> 00:04:25,830
No!

57
00:04:28,760 --> 00:04:30,160
What are you waiting for?

58
00:04:30,760 --> 00:04:31,960
Begin.

59
00:04:36,680 --> 00:04:38,330
Aren't we comparing the rolls?

60
00:04:38,330 --> 00:04:39,520
I actually survived.

61
00:04:39,520 --> 00:04:40,370
Right.

62
00:04:40,730 --> 00:04:42,550
My roll was lower than hers.

63
00:04:42,750 --> 00:04:44,100
I thought I was done for.

64
00:04:45,560 --> 00:04:47,320
Do you remember what that man said?

65
00:04:47,320 --> 00:04:48,360
The dice decide the winner.

66
00:04:48,360 --> 00:04:49,159
Not that part.

67
00:04:49,840 --> 00:04:50,640
Could it be...

68
00:04:50,840 --> 00:04:53,000
The mute servant will announce the winner.

69
00:04:53,000 --> 00:04:53,930
That's the part.

70
00:04:54,120 --> 00:04:55,880
So you mean

71
00:04:56,720 --> 00:04:57,990
our victory or defeat

72
00:04:58,020 --> 00:04:59,520
is decided by the mute servant?

73
00:04:59,520 --> 00:05:00,470
Yes.

74
00:05:01,110 --> 00:05:03,590
Then how does the mute servant
know who wins?

75
00:05:03,610 --> 00:05:06,530
So our lives are in their hands?

76
00:05:06,760 --> 00:05:08,020
Then how do we beat this game?

77
00:05:08,020 --> 00:05:09,620
I haven't figured it out yet.

78
00:05:09,800 --> 00:05:11,360
I need to watch a little longer.

79
00:05:11,360 --> 00:05:13,480
Maybe I'll find a way through.

80
00:05:17,120 --> 00:05:19,680
Master, the new minted coins are here.

81
00:05:19,720 --> 00:05:20,920
Please inspect them.

82
00:05:30,250 --> 00:05:31,410
Well done.

83
00:05:32,320 --> 00:05:33,590
With these,

84
00:05:34,450 --> 00:05:35,850
it won't be long before

85
00:05:36,080 --> 00:05:37,159
the world

86
00:05:37,320 --> 00:05:39,350
belongs to Lingya Tower.

87
00:05:42,370 --> 00:05:44,610
[Long Live Lingya]

88
00:05:52,440 --> 00:05:54,700
Round two of the Golden Cup Guessing Game

89
00:05:55,080 --> 00:05:55,800
begins.

90
00:06:16,480 --> 00:06:17,010
[Token]

91
00:06:18,640 --> 00:06:21,000
The token has different patterns
on each side.

92
00:06:21,000 --> 00:06:21,960
Come on.

93
00:06:36,080 --> 00:06:38,010
No more touching once it's shaken.

94
00:06:48,159 --> 00:06:49,120
Murder!

95
00:06:52,360 --> 00:06:53,680
Why did she kill again?

96
00:06:53,680 --> 00:06:55,400
Weren't the rules clear?

97
00:06:55,840 --> 00:06:57,240
Only one person can win.

98
00:06:57,280 --> 00:06:59,170
So as long as
she gets rid of her opponent,

99
00:06:59,170 --> 00:07:00,540
no matter the outcome,

100
00:07:00,840 --> 00:07:02,000
she survives.

101
00:07:02,020 --> 00:07:04,280
Looks like there are no rules here at all.

102
00:07:05,400 --> 00:07:06,200
To win,

103
00:07:07,000 --> 00:07:08,320
she'll do anything.

104
00:07:09,280 --> 00:07:11,280
Good thing I wasn't paired with her.

105
00:07:11,360 --> 00:07:13,720
Who exactly is this woman?

106
00:07:14,280 --> 00:07:17,160
I heard
she's a centurion of the Chilian Clan.

107
00:07:17,680 --> 00:07:19,360
The number of people who died at her hands

108
00:07:19,360 --> 00:07:21,760
might be more than
the people who died here.

109
00:07:23,600 --> 00:07:25,030
Are we continuing or not?

110
00:07:25,280 --> 00:07:26,160
Begin.

111
00:07:39,040 --> 00:07:39,880
Hey.

112
00:07:40,310 --> 00:07:41,750
Why haven't you opened it yet?

113
00:07:41,750 --> 00:07:43,150
What are you waiting for?

114
00:07:52,980 --> 00:07:54,020
Five.

115
00:07:54,970 --> 00:07:57,100
[Token]

116
00:07:57,700 --> 00:07:59,110
[Token]

117
00:07:59,150 --> 00:08:00,680
The smooth side means high.

118
00:08:00,710 --> 00:08:02,370
So the other side means low.

119
00:08:02,840 --> 00:08:05,910
[Token]

120
00:08:04,510 --> 00:08:06,420
Dao bet on low.

121
00:08:08,100 --> 00:08:09,240
That's my dice!

122
00:08:09,270 --> 00:08:09,900
Give it back!

123
00:08:09,900 --> 00:08:11,170
I won! I won!

124
00:08:11,200 --> 00:08:12,000
My dice!

125
00:08:12,000 --> 00:08:13,080
You two bet on low.

126
00:08:13,100 --> 00:08:14,530
I won!

127
00:08:15,120 --> 00:08:16,000
Looks like

128
00:08:16,160 --> 00:08:17,040
one of you

129
00:08:17,040 --> 00:08:19,240
has figured out the rules.

130
00:08:20,210 --> 00:08:21,810
You've got the wrong person!

131
00:08:21,920 --> 00:08:23,280
There's nothing in her dice!

132
00:08:23,280 --> 00:08:24,410
I should have won!

133
00:08:24,440 --> 00:08:25,880
I should have won!

134
00:08:26,200 --> 00:08:28,280
No, my hat!

135
00:08:28,400 --> 00:08:31,200
-You've got the wrong person!
-My hat! My hat!

136
00:08:32,960 --> 00:08:34,020
Let me go!

137
00:08:34,240 --> 00:08:35,419
Let me go!

138
00:08:36,059 --> 00:08:36,900
Hat!

139
00:08:37,090 --> 00:08:38,590
My hat!

140
00:08:56,320 --> 00:08:57,360
Are you okay?

141
00:08:57,380 --> 00:08:58,440
I'm fine.

142
00:08:58,460 --> 00:08:59,020
Here.

143
00:09:04,980 --> 00:09:05,820
Thank you.

144
00:09:13,690 --> 00:09:14,490
Sis.

145
00:09:16,410 --> 00:09:18,030
You were bitten by a snake.

146
00:09:18,160 --> 00:09:19,000
Are you okay?

147
00:09:19,130 --> 00:09:19,890
I'm fine.

148
00:09:20,020 --> 00:09:20,910
Guards.

149
00:09:21,200 --> 00:09:22,280
Take her away

150
00:09:22,280 --> 00:09:23,400
and lock her up for two hours.

151
00:09:23,400 --> 00:09:24,240
Why?

152
00:09:24,840 --> 00:09:25,720
What are you doing?

153
00:09:25,720 --> 00:09:26,650
Don't come here!

154
00:09:27,200 --> 00:09:29,160
She disrupted the order,

155
00:09:29,320 --> 00:09:30,650
so she must be punished.

156
00:09:30,760 --> 00:09:32,640
If you interfere again,

157
00:09:32,720 --> 00:09:34,780
I'll throw you into the snake pit too.

158
00:09:35,870 --> 00:09:36,910
Dao.

159
00:09:37,640 --> 00:09:38,630
It's fine.

160
00:09:38,680 --> 00:09:39,410
Don't worry.

161
00:09:47,820 --> 00:09:48,870
Nan Yanzhi.

162
00:09:49,060 --> 00:09:50,020
Don't worry.

163
00:09:51,760 --> 00:09:52,960
What a pity.

164
00:09:53,640 --> 00:09:56,170
She probably
won't make it through the night.

165
00:09:56,280 --> 00:09:57,400
What do you mean?

166
00:10:00,560 --> 00:10:02,480
Dao, what does that mean?

167
00:10:02,580 --> 00:10:04,060
What do we do now?

168
00:10:59,760 --> 00:11:00,840
Master.

169
00:11:03,040 --> 00:11:04,240
Master.

170
00:11:07,800 --> 00:11:09,880
I knew you would come to save me.

171
00:11:10,160 --> 00:11:11,820
How many times have I told you?

172
00:11:11,840 --> 00:11:13,760
The prisoners in Lingya Tower
are all serious criminals.

173
00:11:13,760 --> 00:11:14,960
You can't trust them so easily.

174
00:11:14,960 --> 00:11:17,120
Today, for someone you barely know,

175
00:11:17,120 --> 00:11:18,320
you risked your life.

176
00:11:18,480 --> 00:11:20,140
Are you trying to drive me mad?

177
00:11:21,160 --> 00:11:22,120
But

178
00:11:30,760 --> 00:11:31,920
you also said

179
00:11:32,320 --> 00:11:35,040
entering Lingya Tower
means almost certain death.

180
00:11:35,040 --> 00:11:36,190
If that's the case,

181
00:11:36,320 --> 00:11:38,650
then I need real friends.

182
00:11:40,360 --> 00:11:42,520
So you were foolish enough
to risk your life

183
00:11:42,520 --> 00:11:43,640
to make friends?

184
00:11:45,000 --> 00:11:47,320
Do you know how dangerous
the snakes down there are?

185
00:11:47,320 --> 00:11:48,600
Good thing I was here.

186
00:11:49,280 --> 00:11:50,800
Otherwise, you wouldn't even

187
00:11:50,800 --> 00:11:52,530
be able to get out of here today.

188
00:11:56,760 --> 00:11:58,760
Are these snakes really that venomous?

189
00:11:58,760 --> 00:12:00,560
But I still haven't found
my mother's antidote.

190
00:12:00,560 --> 00:12:01,490
What should I do?

191
00:12:07,080 --> 00:12:08,520
But don't worry.

192
00:12:08,980 --> 00:12:10,560
The snake venom isn't fatal.

193
00:12:10,560 --> 00:12:11,840
It only knocks people out,

194
00:12:11,840 --> 00:12:12,970
as if they were dead.

195
00:12:13,560 --> 00:12:14,920
Once the toxin wears off,

196
00:12:14,920 --> 00:12:15,960
you will be fine.

197
00:12:19,760 --> 00:12:21,240
It's not venomous?

198
00:12:21,640 --> 00:12:23,470
Master, why didn't you say so?

199
00:12:23,800 --> 00:12:25,080
You scared me to death.

200
00:12:25,640 --> 00:12:27,440
If I don't teach you a lesson now,

201
00:12:27,520 --> 00:12:28,920
you'll never learn.

202
00:12:30,800 --> 00:12:32,530
I can't watch over you forever.

203
00:12:33,160 --> 00:12:34,820
I have important things to do.

204
00:12:37,000 --> 00:12:37,760
Right.

205
00:12:39,080 --> 00:12:40,880
If the people
thrown into the Ten Thousand Snake Pit

206
00:12:40,880 --> 00:12:41,950
didn't die,

207
00:12:42,640 --> 00:12:43,960
where did they go?

